
# 2026-07-07 15:18:01.666927
+# Project context (cached - do not restate, just apply):
+
+# Claude Orchestrator — Multi-Project Task Executor
+
+**Tech Stack:** Nuxt 3 (Vue 3 SSR) + Supabase + Vercel (web) · Python 3.11+ (runner) · Anthropic API v1 · pgvector + Postgres
+
+**Mission:** Distributed execution of Claude Code across all your projects. Auto-route tasks by cost/throughput via bandit learning. All changes require human approval before merging.
+
+## Directory Map
+
+| Path | Purpose |
+|------|---------|
+| `web/` | Nuxt 3 SPA dashboard (Vercel-hosted) |
+| `runner/` | Python task executor (runs on your Mac) |
+| `supabase/` | Migrations, RLS policies, edge functions |
+| `runner/runner.py` | Main loop: poll → claim → execute → verify → integrate |
+| `runner/bandit.py` | Model selection via UCB1 (cost/throughput) |
+| `runner/account_pool.py` | Rotate API keys across **authorized** accounts |
+| `runner/caching.py` | Stable cached prefix (token savings) |
+| `runner/knowledge.py` | pgvector semantic search + embeddings |
+| `runner/verify.py` | Cheap-model review before integration |
+| `runner/eval_harness.py` | Self-improvement: propose, test, gate, approve |
+| `supabase/functions/` | Slack notifications, approvals webhook |
+
+## Key Concepts
+
+### Task Execution Flow
+```
+1. User queues task from web dashboard (or API)
+   └─ Task: prompt + project_id + deps
+2. Runner polls Supabase, claims task → RUNNING
+3. Runner creates git worktree for project
+4. Runner executes: CLAUDE_BIN=claude python3 runner.py
+   └─ Claude Code runs in isolation, reports back
+5. Verify step: cheap model reviews diff
+   └─ If risky → approval card → web dashboard
+   └─ If safe → integrate (git commit + push)
+6. Outcome recorded: cost ($), tokens, status
+7. Dashboard reflects live changes in real-time
+```
+
+### Multi-Account Rotation
+- `account_pool.py` cycles across your **authorized Anthropic accounts**
+- Routes by usage: picks account with lowest usage when exhausted
+- ⚠️ **SAFETY:** Only use accounts you're entitled to. Stay within Anthropic's usage policies.
+- Model router heuristic (cost vs. throughput) when cold; bandit learning kicks in after ~100 runs
+
+### Knowledge Reuse
+- `knowledge.py` + pgvector: semantic embedding of prior outcomes
+- New task → embed prompt → find similar past solutions
+- Cached context prefix (stable 16k-32k token block) reduces input cost
+
+### Self-Improvement Loop
+- `eval_harness.py` reads telemetry (token spend, failure patterns)
+- Proposes orchestrator prompt improvements as **approval cards**
+- Never self-edits silently — all material changes via git + CI + your approval
+- A/B gates prompt changes before adoption
+
+## Build, Test & Deploy Commands
+
+```bash
+# Web (Nuxt)
+cd web
+npm install
+npm run dev          # http://localhost:3000
+npm run build        # Production build
+npm run preview      # Preview prod build
+
+# Runner (Python)
+cd runner
+pip3 install pyyaml
+python3 runner.py    # Main loop (requires SUPABASE_SERVICE_KEY in .env)
+
+# Test runner execution
+python3 runner.py --dry-run --task-id <id>
+python3 runner.py --project-only tomorrow  # Run only tasks for one project
+
+# Generate task DAG from prompt
+CLAUDE_BIN=claude python3 runner/planner.py "Build X end-to-end" > tasks.yaml
+
+# Supabase
+supabase link --project-ref eatfwdzfurujcuwlhdgj
+supabase db push          # Apply migrations
+supabase functions deploy # Deploy edge functions (Slack)
+```
+
+## Configuration & Secrets
+
+### Web (.env.local / Vercel)
+```bash
+SUPABASE_URL=https://eatfwdzfurujcuwlhdgj.supabase.co
+SUPABASE_KEY=<anon-key>  # Public key (safe to expose)
+```
+
+### Runner (.env, NEVER commit)
+```bash
+SUPABASE_URL=https://eatfwdzfurujcuwlhdgj.supabase.co
+SUPABASE_SERVICE_KEY=<service-role-key>  # SECRET — only runner uses this
+ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-...  # Primary account
+MAX_PARALLEL=2            # Concurrent task executions
+TEST_CMD="npm test"       # Command to run task validation
+INTEGRATION_MODE=pr       # Optional: open PRs instead of pushing
+```
+
+### Multi-Account Setup (account_pool.py)
+- Define in `runner/.env.accounts`:
+  ```bash
+  ACCOUNT_1_KEY=sk-proj-...  (primary)
+  ACCOUNT_2_KEY=sk-proj-...
+  ACCOUNT_3_KEY=sk-proj-...
+  ```
+- Runner rotates when any account exhausted
+- Falls back to model heuristic (cost/throughput) when usage unclear
+
+**Rule:** Only rotate accounts you're authorized to use. Verify Anthropic's usage policies.
+
+## Database Schema
+
+| Table | Purpose |
+|-------|---------|
+| `projects` | Name, repo path, budget cap, model preferences |
+| `tasks` | Prompt, status, project_id, dependencies, cost |
+| `approvals` | Risky diffs awaiting review (Why/Value/Risk) |
+| `outcomes` | Result, cost ($), tokens used, error log |
+| `accounts` | Metadata per API account (rotation, usage) |
+| `runner_heartbeats` | Runner health + cost burn-down |
+| `knowledge` | Embeddings + outcomes for semantic search |
+| `budgets` | Per-project spend caps ($/month) |
+| `failures` | Error patterns + recovery suggestions |
+
+**RLS:** Members read/act on tasks; runner uses service role (append-only on outcomes).
+
+## DO / DON'T
+
+**DO:**
+- Approve material changes (all self-edits, multi-project diffs) before merge
+- Test execution with `--dry-run` before running real task
+- Set project budgets in `budgets` table (prevents runaway spend)
+- Rotate accounts fairly — don't exhaust one while others idle
+- Use contract-first DAGs (task 1 = shared types/API, deps lock in contract early)
+- Review `verify.py` diffs carefully before approving (risky = needs review)
+- Schedule runner via launchd (plist) for durability — reuse `scripts/setup-scheduler.sh`
+- Keep `runner/.env` out of git — add to `.gitignore` if missing
+- Handle transient errors (HTTP 409) in central location; treat as requeues not terminal
+- Implement fallbacks for missing/malformed data (use best-effort ranking)
+- Trust worktree_gc: it only removes stale worktrees from completed tasks (never RUNNING/RETRY tasks)
+
+**DON'T:**
+- Commit `runner/.env`, `web/.env`, or any `SUPABASE_SERVICE_KEY` to git
+- Use unauthorized Anthropic accounts (violates usage policy)
+- Skip approval cards — self-changes must go through git + CI + your approval
+- Run raw SQL via shell; use Supabase migrations for schema changes
+- Hardcode project paths — query `projects` table for repo_path
+- Exhaust one account while leaving others idle — bandit learns, but rotate fairly
+- Assume outcomes cached forever — re-embed knowledge on schema updates
+- Bypass RLS policies with direct untyped queries
+- Rely on specific error codes (409, etc.) — handle HTTP errors by behavior (transient vs. terminal)
+- Hardcode error messages — use generic error handling approach
+
+## Development & Debugging
+
+### Runner troubleshooting
+```bash
+# Check runner health
+tail -f ~/.local/share/claude-orchestrator/runner.log
+
+# Inspect a task state
+supabase sql "SELECT * FROM tasks WHERE id = 'task-123'"
+
+# Replay a task
+python3 runner.py --replay-task <task-id>
+
+# Test Supabase connection
+python3 -c "from runner.knowledge import knowledge_client; print(knowledge_client.table('projects').select('*').execute())"
+```
+
+### Dashboard (web/) — Nuxt
+- Vue 3 + Tailwind; auto-import components
+- `pages/index.vue` — dashboard (live task board)
+- `pages/queue.vue` — queue a task form
+- `components/ApprovalCard.vue` — shows Why/Value/Risk
+- `components/SpendChart.vue` — Chart.js burn-down
+- Real-time updates via Supabase subscriptions
+
+### Model selection (bandit.py)
+- Starts with heuristics: faster models for parsing, bigger for generation
+- Learns best model per workload type (cost-per-token vs. throughput)
+- UCB1 (Upper Confidence Bound) balances exploitation vs. exploration
+- Reset via: `UPDATE accounts SET model_stats = NULL WHERE id = 'account-1'`
+
+## Security & Hygiene
+
+- **No secrets in code:** `.env` git-ignored, only `.env.example` committed
+- **Service role scoped:** Runner uses service role (append-only); members use anon auth
+- **API rate limits:** 2 MB body max; per-user/IP rate limits enforced
+- **Audit trail:** All AI calls logged (model, tokens, cost); outcomes immutable
+- **Verify before merge:** `verify.py` cheap-model reviews diffs; risky = approval required
+
+## Deployment Checklist
+
+- [ ] **Supabase:** Project linked, migrations applied, RLS policies active
+- [ ] **Web:** Built locally (`npm run build`), deployed to Vercel, env vars set
+- [ ] **Runner:** Python deps installed, `.env` configured (not committed), launchd plist created
+- [ ] **Test E2E:** Queue a small task, confirm runner claims → verify → integrate → dashboard updates
+- [ ] **Secrets audit:** `git log -p | grep -i service_role` returns nothing; `.gitignore` covers `*.env`
+- [ ] **Budget caps:** Set per-project spend limits in `budgets` table
+- [ ] **Slack (optional):** Deploy edge functions if notifications needed
+
+## Integration with Tomorrow / Smarter / Apparently
+
+This orchestrator can manage all three repos in parallel:
+- Register each in `projects` table (name + repo_path)
+- Runner polls all, respects per-project budgets
+- `knowledge.py` embeds solutions across all projects
+- Self-improvement learns from all outcomes
+
+**Cross-project contract-first DAGs:** Task 1 defines shared API, all deps lock into contract early.
+
+## Notes
+
+- Supabase (ref: `eatfwdzfurujcuwlhdgj`) is live
+- Runner is **not** in Supabase functions; it's a Python script on your Mac for full control (terminal, git creds, Claude CLI auth)
+- Web is thin client — all logic in runner + Supabase
+- **Cost tracking:** Every Claude call logged; budgets prevent runaway spend
+
